According to VWS Wildfire Services, the fire started on Sunday and expanded rapidly.The VWS Wildfire Services has urged motorists to stay clear of the area and let fire services do their work.The Du Toitskloof Pass has been reopened following extensive mountain fires near the Paarl area.The fire broke out last week, destroying about 1500 hectares of land.Western Cape Disaster Management warned last week Friday of dry, hot conditions and strong winds increasing the risk of fires on the West Coast.